
# have you ever fantasize  of making your own web page, but suddenly you remember that you have no experience in coding , well what if i told you that you dont need to be experienced in coding because with the (markDown language ) your idea could come to life thanks to github and github pages its really easy and simple .

# but of course when we say easy that does not mean you dont have to spend some time reading about it thankfully there is not much reading requierd to make a simple site just look at these few examples and then you can start building your dream page .
* here its some basic elemts in the
 # markDown language

# 1- first of all texts:  its as easy as writing simple English 

# example :
>It's very easy to make some words  `<**bold**>` and other words `<*italic*>` with Markdown.

# result:

It's very easy to make some words *bold* and other words _italic_ with Markdown. 
# example : 
 #header1

##header2
###header3

######header6

 # result : 

  # header1

## header2

 ### header3

###### header6

# links 

[link to Google!](google link )

#result : 

[link to Google!](http://google.com)
# 2- Images 

# example:
>  If you want to embed images, this is how you do it:. `<![Image of petra](https://www.arabiaweddings.com/sites/default/files/uploads/2016/05/12/the_petra.jpg)>`

result:
If you want to embed images, this is how you do it:

![Image of petra](https://www.arabiaweddings.com/sites/default/files/uploads/2016/05/12/the_petra.jpg)

# 3- Lists
# example:

>Unordered
* coffe
* tea
  * milk
  * green tea
  # result:
 

Unordered
* cofee
* tea
  * milk
  * green tea
 # example:  
>Ordered

>1. Item 1
1. Item 2
1. Item 3
   

   # result:

1- Item 1

2- Item 2

3- Item 3

# tables:

`<First Header | Second Header>`

`<------------ | ------------->`

`<Content from cell 1 | Content from cell 2>`

`<Content in the first column | Content in the second column>`

# result:
First Header | Second Header
------------ | -------------
Content from cell 1 | Content from cell 2
Content in the first column | Content in the second column

